SIMPLE: sadly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sadly
<hw>Sad"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wearily; heavily;
firmly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In go the spears full <qex>sadly</qex> in arest.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Seriously; soberly; gravely.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To tell thee <qex>sadly</qex>, shepherd, without blame⟦br⟧
Or our neglect, we lost her as we came.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Grievously; deeply; sorrowfully; miserably.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧He <xex>sadly</xex> suffers in their grief.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sadness</ent>⟦br⟧
